<br>
I went into Najena with the intent to get some focus items. I'm a 25 magician. I first tried killing tentacle terros just because I've never been there and I thought maybe I'd give my pet a tentalce whip. I got run out twice by add skeletons, and later as I went slightly deeper, add elementals.<br>
<br>
I'd never been to Najena before. My gear is horrible (this is an old magician pre-Kunark that I'm dusting off) and wonder about level suggestions or other warnings or advice from those familiar with the zone. You know, where a poorly outfitted 25 mage should avoid, or even what level to come back at!<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, I've only seen one shovel for sale in bazaar for 500pp. I have some of the other items I've kept a hold of over the last couple of years, but looking to get the torch, stein, etc.<br>
<br>
Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barmodius>Barmodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(2/1/03 8:57:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1042.topic&index=24>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus Item Quest</span><hr size=1> It is terrible that someone had the shovel for 500pp. I hope it wasn't a mage. Last time I camped Najena for my final item (broom), I ended up with an extra stein and shovel, which I sold at bazaar for 10pp each. Had there been a mage there of appropriate level, I would have given them gladly. Najena is just a fat timesink.<br>
<br>
At 25 and solo, I would suggest you stick strictly to the magicians. Avoid the TT by staying in the middle of the large room when going through it. Summon an earth pet and have it at all times. If things go terribly wrong, it will buy you enough time to zone or gate.   The skeletons there are around lvl 21-24.  You can take them, just watch for adds.  <br>
<br>
There are 4 magicians that you can safely solo at 25. There are two together in the Crystal room, and 2 singles on the path to the crystal room. These can all be taken effectively at 25. Sic your pet on the other pet first, then burn the magician down as fast as possible.<br>
<br>
Stay away from the magicians in Rathyl's room and Trazdon's room. You can take them, but at 25, Trazdon, Rathyl, and Rathyl's incarnate will hand you your butt in tiny, manageable chunks. It is still a close shave at 42 to break the Rathyl room.<br>
<br>
Best advice, get some resist gear. You are going against mage and necro casters, so get your magic, fire, and poison resists pretty high. A couple of Star Ruby Encrusted Steins will help greatly.<br>
<br>
And keep checking the bazaar. I've rarely seen the focus ingredients very high. You might get lucky and get them for about 10pp. <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:Blur(Add = 1, Direction = 225, Strength = 10)">
